{"id": "EUVD-2025-5151", "enisaUuid": "dfda8a1c-e88c-3ae7-84f2-164c3010402b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nipv6: mcast: add RCU protection to mld_newpack()\n\nmld_newpack() can be called without RTNL or RCU being held.\n\nNote that we no longer can use sock_alloc_send_skb() because\nipv6.igmp_sk uses GFP_KERNEL allocations which can sleep.\n\nInstead use alloc_skb() and charge the net->ipv6.igmp_sk\nsocket under RCU protection.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T02:18:12", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T19:37:03", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-21758", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1b91c597b0214b1b462eb627ec02658c944623f2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/25195f9d5ffcc8079ad743a50c0409dbdc48d98a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a527750d877fd334de87eef81f1cb5f0f0ca3373", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d60d493b0e65647e0335e6a7c4547abcea7df8e9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e8af3632a7f2da83e27b083f787bced1faba00b1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/29fa42197f26a97cde29fa8c40beddf44ea5c8f3", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00028.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21758", "GHSA-xv46-47mw-9vxc"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3106b85d-ca0b-3655-8715-2a1652a80efe", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b8ad0cbc58f703972e9e37c4e2a8081dd7e6a551 <1b91c597b0214b1b462eb627ec02658c944623f2"}, {"id": "5496562f-a0d6-334b-a214-a8cc89aee4e5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.179"}, {"id": "561983a9-499d-3f52-aa0f-d87f26ef6e37", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "7e77471c-c80e-3d57-99dc-6f37de8eb3f9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13.4"}, {"id": "7ef47ec3-e560-3107-973f-0dd301c394eb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b8ad0cbc58f703972e9e37c4e2a8081dd7e6a551 <a527750d877fd334de87eef81f1cb5f0f0ca3373"}, {"id":